Czech Shares Advance for Sixth Day, Led by AAA Auto, NWR, Erste

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-03-30T10:45:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/czech-shares-advance-for-sixth-day-led-by-aaa-auto-nwr-erste.html
The Czech Republic’s main equity
index rose for a sixth day, heading for its longest stretch of
gains in more than eight months, led by  AAA Auto Group NV (AAA) ,  New
World Resources NV (NWR)  and  Erste Group Bank AG. (EBS)   The PX gauge of 15 stocks advanced 0.4 percent to 1,263.7
as of 12:20 p.m. in  Prague , extending its gains so far this
month to 1.6 percent. A close at this level would be the index’s
highest in more than two months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
